jobDescription:
Abstract: 
Due to their lower deployment cost, Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) have been more
intensively used in various applications such as healthcare, industry, environment monitor,
etc. However, their advantages pose some challenges because of their design complexity
that is considered as one of the most signicant barriers to the widespread
adoption of WSNs but also offers new opportunities for researchers to break down these
trade-offs. With this purpose, this thesis concentrates on two selected topics that have
signicant impact on WSNs performance. These topics are as follows: An accurate and
low cost localization systems, Energy efficient cluster based routing approaches.

I am an engineer (MSME) from Germany, and interested in medical engineering.
In total I earned about 2 years of medical engineering research experience as an undergraduate and graduate student respectively. My main projects concerned the accuracy and precision of roentgen stereometric analysis in the spinal region, as well as the use of the technique in clinical trials (hip replacements, spinal range of motion), mechanical cadaver and osteosynthesis plate testing within orthopaedics, shape memory material (nitinol) testing in ENT as well as tissue slicing, viability testing and vitrification in rat kidney slice preservation. 
As an intern at Brainlab AG in Munich I helped with the usability of navigation systems for ENT and spinal surgery.
I attended several surgeries in ENT and orthopaedics giving me further insights into the needs of medical care.

Ingrid started her career as a Web application developer in the late 90s.  Having experience with both interactive agencies and venture-funded, she co-founded a boutique development shop, Quick Left in 2010 in downtown Boulder.

Quick Left grew quickly and was acquired by Cognizant in 2016, with the purpose of developing an internal startup Accelerator. The group expanded to over 1000 people globally and grew into Cognizant‚Äôs internal product division for a time. The Accelerator team exceeded diversity numbers for the rest of the company as well as market competitors.

She left Cognizant in 2020 to become a General Partner at Stage Fund, a private equity firm making control investments in pre-scale companies. She primarily focuses on portfolio operations and technology due diligence, including rolling up her sleeves to help the companies grow to the next level.

Ingrid loves working with people, making connections, motivating, collaborating and solving problems. She is a sought-after public speaker, having won numerous awards including Entrepreneur of the Year. Quick Left made the Inc. 500 list of fastest growing companies a few years in a row. Ingrid served as Chair of the Board for Turing School of Software and Design for 6 years and has been a mentor for Boulder-based TechStars Accelerator. Her personal belief is that successful technologies lie in the intersection of technology and human connection. While she's no longer writing code, she'll always be an engineer at heart, thinking strategically about providing impactful solutions. 

Ingrid lives in Boulder, Colorado with her 6-year-old twin girls. In a past life, she was on the US Cycling team as well as a competitive nordic skier. She‚Äôs traded in her gear for a pair of running shoes for new athletic challenges ahead. And to keep up with her girls who are now ripping up the slopes and the local bike park.

Everyone is talking about athlete development, but Re-Play is actually using proven science, structured curriculum and professionally proven training to assist athletes achieve more focused results, faster. Our revolutionary, patent-pending apps deliver, track, guide, showcase and share player development. Internet of Things Based Supply chain management(SCM): This thesis mainly aimed to design new efficient security algorithms and tracking schemes intended for IoT based supply chain. The main contributions of this thesis consist of the design of:

- A context-aware middleware for RFID based pharmacy supply chain, which aims to offer a deeper intelligence for the objects monitoring.A variant of Fosstrack middleware was proposed to offer a deeper intelligence in the RFID based supply chain. 
- A traceability layered model that captures the key ingredients of the IoT network and provides a formal representation to a tracking system.  
- A secured distributed supply chain architecture based on Merkle tree. 
This thesis resulted in 7 scientific papers accepted at reknown international conferences and journals.

Just scanning through? Here's my elevator pitch:

I am currently pursuing a master‚Äôs in disaster management and resilience. I‚Äôve worked as a coordinator, researcher, and most recently in business logistics, and am actively engaged in multiple volunteer positions with the Canadian Red Cross. I am looking for a job that will put my skills as a researcher and disaster manager to work in our fight against climate change.

Curious to know more?

As a kid in the Swiss countryside, I would often walk the extra mile from school with a bucket full of rescued toads to release them in our local protected pond. Nobody asked me to; I just knew that it was the right thing to do. Climate change wasn‚Äôt the only culprit for the toads‚Äô degraded environment; urban planning just didn‚Äôt include environmental sustainability back then.

My drive for environmental justice steered me through my biology degree and transformed my initial adoration of nature into a comprehensive knowledge of ecology and biodiversity, with a focus on sustainability practices and ecosystem management. My adventurous personality led me through multiple cultural volunteer and work contexts, away from the lab coat and into the world of international development and humanitarian action management. 

My forces are best expressed when working with and for people. I am a fast-adapting, trilingual - English, French, and German - multitasker, always looking to learn. My specialties include prevention, problem-solving, analytical thinking, research, and reporting. I am equally happy on the G-Suite (Google sheets, docs, and slides) as I am on Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint), and if it can be automated, it will.

My long-term professional goal is to provide organizational support within the ecosystem-based DRR and CCA sectors. I am determined to help alleviate harm and mitigate loss through nature-based solutions. I am still enthusiastically exploring learning opportunities, my two latest recommendations being the Sustainable Development in Humanitarian Action course by the IFRC, and the Nature-based Solutions for Disaster and Climate Resilience MOOC by the UNEP.

Feel free to get in touch, even if it's just to chat about travels, have an open conversation about mental health, exchange learning tips, or just connect, from one human being to another.

description:
During my childhood, I used to dismantle all kinds of game/electronic gadgets at sight to understand how they work and how they do. To find out more about this, I have chosen to study engineering and I have succeeded to be graduated as an Electromechanical engineer. In addition to that, I have attended a postgraduate program in petroleum engineering at the Oil & Gas Institute of Monastir (OGIM).

My first professional experience started while attending university. I have experienced working part-time as a technical assistant in one of the most prestigious corporations in this field. I have gained decent experience by handling customers‚Äô complaints, answering inquiries about products specification via phone, providing troubleshooting for various technical issues, and so forth. By working in this position, I have developed my communication skills and improved my French language level, since French is the only spoken language by our foreign customers.

After graduating, I landed a job as a manufacturing process engineer at the reputable German multinational company LEONI Wiring System in my home country Tunisia. By working for LEONI, I have gained a decent experience in the automotive industry and I‚Äôm a crucial member of the manufacturing process team.
Skilled in the field of Process and method engineering, communication, time management & organization, and problem-solving.

I‚Äôm eager to stretch the limits of my knowledge and experience in mechanical/electrical and petroleum engineering. Therefore, I‚Äôm looking for interesting opportunities to reach my goals and unlock my professional dreams.

To find out more about my educational background, work experiences, training, and language certificates please refer to my attached CV.

Please feel free to reach me either via LinkedIn, email, or phone.

jobDescription2:
Manufacturing process engineer in the automotive industry

Process: Ultrasonic Welding and Heat Shrinking operation

‚Ä¢ Defining & organizing the production process in accordance with customer requirements and LEONI's work instructions.

‚Ä¢ Conduct research, and consider alternative approaches to improve production process performance by applying Lean Manufacturing & GMP.

‚Ä¢ Create specifications (SOW) for manufacturing equipment

‚Ä¢ Choose & order equipment for ultrasonic welding and heat shrinking, define and order spare parts.

‚Ä¢ Constantly attend meetings with international suppliers to discuss engineering-related issues and possible improvements (Schunk, Mecalbi, DSG-Canusa, Raychem,..)

‚Ä¢ Installation, approval, and requalification of all shrinking and welding machines (IQ / OQ / PQ)

‚Ä¢ Defining ultrasonic welding parameters, programming weld generators, and approving weld combinations.

‚Ä¢ Coordinating and implementing activities for changes in the ultrasonic welding and heat shrinking process in accordance with change management and project management.

‚Ä¢ Carry out weekly process audits, and analyse garnered data so as to find out potential betterments in the existing process.

‚Ä¢ Draw and develop mechanical designs and detailed drawings using SolidWorks software for required mechanical components and assemblies that meet performance and cost targets

‚Ä¢ Prepare for and participate in design review meetings with suppliers.

‚Ä¢ Cooperate with the maintenance department to troubleshoot problems and downtime on machines in production.

‚Ä¢ Train and guide production staff to ensure adherence to required methods and processes.

‚Ä¢ Provide engineering support to the production maintenance team to solve critical/rare problems on equipment.

‚Ä¢ Attend and participate in PFMEA, RFMEA & QRQC scheduled meetings.

‚Ä¢ Update process documents (work instructions, control instructions).

‚Ä¢ Draw up and update machines' documents (Maintenance Plan, Setup Parameters, Auto Maintenace)

Project :
- Talenteo is a Cloud Native HRIS solution which covers all the management processes of an HRM: recruitments, trainings, missions, editing and sending resumes, co-optations, monitoring and evaluation of consultants. The platform is developed with Angular on the Front-End and Spring Boot on the Back End.

Goal :
- Automate CI/CD chains to deploy a Cloud Native HRIS solution called "Talenteo" on a Kubernetes Cluster managed by Microsoft Azure (AKS) using Azure DevOps.

Tasks :
* Configure a pipeline to provision an Azure infrastructure using Terraform (Cluster AKS, Blob Storage, Azure Container Registry, Vnet et Subnets).
* Setting up three namespaces on AKS (Dev, Int, Prod).
* Deploy PostgreSQL in Statefulset on AKS using Helm and configure database schemas and users.
* Dockerize the Back-End micro-services (Spring Boot) with Jib and use a dockerfile to containerize the Front-End part (Angular 9).
* use Helm to make dynamic Kubernetes resources declarations (Ingress, Deployments, Services, Secrets, certificat TLS) by injecting inside the concerned values from a separated files entitled ‚Äúvalues.yml‚Äù. Each desired environment such as Dev, Int or Prod has its own values.
* Implement automated CI/CD pipelines for each microservice and the Front-End part (from GitLab --> Azure DevOps pipelines Build --> Azure DevOps pipelines Release --> AKS).
* Ensure proper cost management on Azure (Kubecost).
* Create Pull Requests for major changes done on existing files in GitLab repos (git).

Technical environment :
- Ubuntu 20.04 LTS (Focal Fossa), Terraform (v0.12), Azure Cli, Kubernetes (v1.19.11), K9s, Helm (v3), Docker, Jib, Azure Portal, Azure DevOps, Azure Artifacts, maven, SonarQube, JaCoCo, Intellij IDE, VS Code, git, GitLab, AKS, Slack, Jira.

description:
My only passion in life has always been computers so, orienting my professional career in engineering field was therefore a logical continuation. 
First, I started by integrating a telecommunications engineer training cycle at the National Advanced School of Posts and Telecommunications of Yaounde (Cameroon) after a year of training at the university of Yaounde I in computer science. I also had the opportunity to have a rich professional experience in particular during my time as a Network Engineer at Camtel (Cameroon), where I had the opportunity to observe and develop the skills required for the efficient conduct of business projects. Then, I followed a training in Cyber Security Engineering in Tunisia since 2014. 
My objective is to work and make a contribution in this field especially in sub-Saharan Africa where it's still very little developed. 

The convergence of networks and operations independently of the companies and their sector of activity have accentuated the issues of cyber security like the banks and their transactions. Many companies, however, remain very uneducated, especially in Africa, where most of the time, these fields are subcontracted. I saw it while I was at ENEO S.A as a trainee between July and August 2016. I believe that our task is to provide the necessary support to encourage companies to become aware of the sensitivity of their assets and thus invest in mechanisms that protect them and thus integrate them into their operating processes.
